# Mobile App – Expo Patterns

## Data layer: Legend-State → Supabase (no SQLite, no Drizzle, no TanStack Query for app data)

All synced data lives in Legend-State observables (`lib/store/index.ts`), persisted to MMKV and synced to Supabase via `syncedSupabase`. Never call the Supabase REST API directly for CRUD — mutate the observables.

```typescript
// Read (reactive) — components use the observable hooks
import { wallets$ } from '@/lib/store';
import { use$ } from '@legendapp/state/react';
const wallets = use$(wallets$);

// Write — via helpers in lib/supabase/*.ts which set() into the store;
// Legend-State syncs to Postgres in the background
wallets$[id].set({ ...wallet, name: 'Updated' });

// Delete — soft delete only (synced tables have a `deleted` column)
```

New synced table checklist: migration adds `created_at`/`updated_at`/`deleted` + RLS + realtime → add observable in `lib/store/index.ts` → CRUD helper in `lib/supabase/`.

## MMKV instances (lib/mmkv/)

- `auth` — Supabase session storage (client uses `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`)
- `legend-store` — observable persistence
- `image-uploads` — receipt upload queue
- `preferences` — local UI prefs (theme: light / dark / system)

## AI pipeline (lib/ai/)

Input → `processing-queue.ts` (MMKV) → `background-processor.ts` (Android FG service) → `run-extraction.ts` → `lib/ai/client` (HTTP → Go backend when `EXPO_PUBLIC_AI_API_URL` set, mock otherwise) → `proposed_transactions` → review modal.

- Client results are `{ status: 'ok' | 'skipped' | 'unavailable' }` — never throw across this boundary
- Wire types in `lib/ai/client/types.ts` must match `apps/backend/internal/extract/types.go`
- Notification prefilter is deterministic and on-device: `lib/notifications/notification-filter.js` (CommonJS — required by the headless task in `index.js` before expo-router loads)

## Routing (expo-router)

`app/(auth)` unauthenticated; `app/(tabs)` main tabs (Wallets / Summary / Moni Agent / Profile); `app/(routes)` stack screens. Auth guard in `app/_layout.tsx`.

## Styling (Uniwind)

Tailwind via Uniwind `className` — **not** NativeWind. Design tokens live in `global.css`:

- Brand scale: `--color-brand-*` in `@theme`
- Semantic light/dark: `--color-background`, `--color-primary`, etc. in `@layer theme` `@variant`
- Screens use semantic utilities (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `bg-canvas`) — never hardcode brand hex
- JS color props (charts, tab bar, icons): `useThemeTokens()` from `@/hooks/use-theme-tokens`
- Theme preference: `lib/theme/preference.ts` → `Uniwind.setTheme('light' | 'dark' | 'system')`; default **light**
- Shared chrome: `components/ui/brand-header`, `screen-shell`, `chip`, `primary-button`

Native modules in use → always test with a dev client (`pnpm --filter moni android`), never Expo Go.
